# Privacy Policy for Misogi

Last updated: January 2, 2025

## Introduction
Thank you for choosing Misogi ("we," "our," or "us"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our Misogi mobile application (the "App"). Please read this privacy policy carefully. If you disagree with its terms, please do not use the App.

## Information We Collect

### Personal Information
We may collect the following types of personal information:
- First and last name
- Contact information
- Social media account information (when you choose to connect accounts)
- Profile pictures
- User-generated content (habits, challenges, adventures, and related metadata)

### Usage Data
We automatically collect certain information about your device and how you interact with our App, including:
- Device type and operating system
- App usage statistics
- Performance data
- Debugging information

### Local Storage and Core Data
The App uses Apple's Core Data framework to store:
- Habit tracking information
- Challenge and adventure records
- Contact information
- Life events and interactions
- Images associated with adventures and logs

## How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information for:
- Providing and maintaining the App's core functionality
- Personalizing your experience
- Tracking your progress with habits and challenges
- Managing social connections and interactions
- Improving and optimizing the App
- Responding to your requests and feedback

## Data Storage and Security

### Local Storage
- Most of your data is stored locally on your device using Core Data
- Images are stored securely within the App's sandbox environment
- Social connection data is encrypted and stored securely

### Cloud Storage
- If you enable iCloud backup, your data will be stored according to Apple's privacy and security standards
- We do not maintain our own cloud storage of your personal data

## Third-Party Services

### Social Media Integration
When you choose to connect social media accounts:
- We only access the information you explicitly authorize
- We follow each platform's authentication and data handling guidelines
- You can revoke access at any time through your profile settings

### Analytics
We use analytics tools to improve the App's performance and user experience:
- Usage patterns and interaction data
- Performance metrics
- Crash reports
- All analytics data is anonymized and aggregated

## Your Rights and Control

You have the right to:
- Access your personal information
- Correct inaccurate data
- Delete your account and associated data
- Opt-out of optional data collection
- Disconnect social media accounts
- Control app permissions (camera, notifications, etc.)

## Children's Privacy

The App is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you become aware that a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.

## Changes to This Policy

We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by:
- Posting the new privacy policy in the App
- Updating the "Last updated" date
- Sending an in-app notification for significant changes

## Your California Privacy Rights

If you are a California resident, you have additional rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA).

## Contact Us

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
rznblbs731@gmail.com

## Consent

By using our App, you consent to our Privacy Policy and agree to its terms.
